            <section class="mt-8 prose">
              <h2>How this Connecticut income tax calculator works</h2>
              <p>
                This tool estimates your
                <strong>Connecticut state income tax</strong> using the latest
                published CT tax brackets and rates for the 2024–2025 filing
                season. It applies a progressive tax structure to your
                <strong>Connecticut taxable income</strong>, then subtracts any
                CT credits you enter to show your net tax.
              </p>
              <p>
                For most people, a quick way to approximate Connecticut taxable
                income is to start from your
                <strong>federal taxable income</strong> and then adjust for
                Connecticut‑specific additions and subtractions (for example,
                certain pension or Social Security exemptions). For precise
                results, use your CT‑1040 worksheets.
              </p>

              <h3>Connecticut income tax brackets (illustrative)</h3>
              <p>
                Connecticut uses a <strong>progressive</strong> income tax
                system. Your income is divided into ranges (“brackets”), and
                each range is taxed at its own rate. The calculator uses a
                bracket table like the one below; exact thresholds may change
                when the legislature updates the law.
              </p>

              <div class="formula-box text-sm">
                <p class="font-semibold mb-2">
                  Example CT tax brackets – Single filers
                </p>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                  <table class="min-w-full text-xs">
                    <thead>
                      <tr class="border-b">
                        <th class="text-left py-1 pr-4">Taxable income</th>
